juniMplsAgent.name: juniMplsAgent

revisions.description: Added agent capabilities definitions for MPLS-LSR-STD-MIB.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added IP TTL Propagate object to the MPLS scalar group.
Added RowStatus support to the minor layer and the tunnel profile groups.
The initial release of this management information module.

juniMplsAgent.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniMplsAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the MultiProtocol Label Switching (MPLS) component of the SNMP agent in the Juniper E-series family of products.

juniMplsAgentV1.name: juniMplsAgentV1
juniMplsAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the MultiProtocol Label Switching (MPLS) component of the
        JUNOSe SNMP agent.  This version of the MPLS component was supported in
        JUNOSe 4.0 system releases.
juniMplsAgentV1.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the MPLS application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when new RowStatus objects were added to the tables in juniMplsMinorLayerConfGroup and juniMplsTunnelProfileConfGroup.

juniMplsAgentV2.name: juniMplsAgentV2
juniMplsAgentV2.productrelease:

juniMplsAgentV2.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the MPLS application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when the IP TTL Propagate object was added to the MPLS scalar group.
